bug.summary: PreTrained VGGFACE appears to be a ComputationGraph
bug.description:
<denchmark-h:h4>Issue Description</denchmark-h>
When trying to use the VGGFACE PretrainedType for Transfer Learning in the SNAPSHOT version, an error occurs because Saved model appears to be a ComputationGraph and the modelType of VGG16 is a MultiLayerNetwork. This has been changed 1 day ago (<denchmark-link:https://github.com/deeplearning4j/deeplearning4j/pull/5149>https://github.com/deeplearning4j/deeplearning4j/pull/5149</denchmark-link> ) I tried redownloading the PreTrained model from "<denchmark-link:http://blob.deeplearning4j.org/models/vgg16_dl4j_vggface_inference.v1.zip>http://blob.deeplearning4j.org/models/vgg16_dl4j_vggface_inference.v1.zip</denchmark-link> " but this didn't work since this downloaded model appears to be a <denchmark-h:h4>Version Information</denchmark-h>
DL4J version: 1.0.0-SNAPSHOT (Note: on 1.0.0-alpha the modelType is ComputationGraph and that one works fine.) Related Issue: <denchmark-link:https://github.com/deeplearning4j/deeplearning4j/issues/5148>https://github.com/deeplearning4j/deeplearning4j/issues/5148</denchmark-link>

comments.comment: Yes, this is definitely the same issue as <denchmark-link:https://github.com/deeplearning4j/deeplearning4j/issues/5148>https://github.com/deeplearning4j/deeplearning4j/issues/5148</denchmark-link>
